{"key":"processedPost-10728010","value":{"id":10728010,"first":10726981,"last":10728010,"when":1248388545,"utime":"07/24/09 01:35 AM","content":"We've had at least three 'should I sterilize the verm' threads this week, and at least three lighting threads.&nbsp; Does nobody even read the forum any more to learn from other people's threads? <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif\" alt=\":shrug:\" title=\":shrug:\"/><br /><br />Yes, you should heat treat the verm.&nbsp; Contrary to incorrect info posted above, verm IS nutritious and will support molds.&nbsp; If it's factory sealed in the bag, you can get away with using it as-is, but if the bag has been opened for awhile, it could have mold spores lurking on the contents.<br /><br />Bright light from a window or fluorescent is superior to dim light.&nbsp; They don't just need light to pin.&nbsp; Mushrooms derive energy from the light and will grow thicker and heavier with better developed caps if exposed to bright light on a normal day/night schedule.<br />RR","title":"Re: light help!!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}